# Near Me — App conventions

## Structure

- Follow App Router: `src/app/` for routes, `src/components/ui|layout|sections` for UI, `src/lib` helpers, `src/hooks`, `src/types`.
- Do not add duplicate folders or one-off files without a clear purpose.

## Components

- Default to Server Components; add `"use client"` only when the file needs browser APIs, hooks, or event handlers.
- Prefer small components; keep files under ~200 lines; no repeated JSX—extract when reused twice.
- PascalCase for components; match existing import and naming style.

## Styling

- Use theme tokens from `globals.css` / Tailwind theme—no hardcoded hex colors for UI.
- Avoid inline styles unless necessary; keep spacing and typography consistent with existing sections.

## Quality

- No `console.log` in code meant for production; remove unused imports and dead commented code.
- Prefer focused diffs: change only what the task needs; avoid drive-by refactors.

## Maps / search UI

- Map and location search live in `NearbySearchSection` and `NearbyMap`; extend existing patterns instead of parallel implementations.
